XMI.documentation.XMI.longDescription: The MOF provides a set of modeling elements, including rules for their use, with which to construct models. Formally, the MOF is defined in itself: in essence the MOF Model is its own metamodel. This file contains the MOF Model expressed as as MOF metamodel, along with the PrimitiveTypes and CorbaIdlTypes metamodels. This file is non-normative.
XMI.documentation.XMI.shortDescription: Definition of the metametamodels for MOF version 1.4, generated according to XMI version 1.1.

Model:Constraint.name: MustBeContainedUnlessPackage
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context ModelElement inv: not self.oclIsTypeOf(Package) implies self.container -> size = 1

Model:Constraint.Model.ModelElement.name: FrozenAttributesCannotBeChanged
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context ModelElement inv: self.isFrozen() implies let myTypes = self.oclType() -> allSupertypes() -> includes(self.oclType()) in let myAttrs : Set(Attribute) = self.RefBaseObject::refMetaObject() -> asOclType(Class) -> findElementsByTypeExtended(Attribute) in myAttrs -> forAll(a | self.RefObject::refValue@pre(a) = self.RefObject::refValue(a))

Model:Constraint.name: FrozenElementsCannotBeDeleted
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context ModelElement post: (self.isFrozen@pre() and self.container@pre -> notEmpty and self.container.isFrozen@pre()) implies (self.container.Object::non_existent() or not self.Object::non_existent())

Model:Constraint.Model.ModelElement.name: FrozenDependenciesCannotBeChanged
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context ModelElement post: self.isFrozen() implies let myClasses = self.oclType() -> allSupertypes() -> includes(self.oclType()) in let myRefs = Set(Reference) = self.RefBaseObject::refMetaObject() -> asOclType(Class) -> findElementsByTypeExtended(Reference) in let myDepRefs = myRefs -> select(r | Set{" " " includes(r.name)) in myDepRefs -> forAll(r | self.RefObject::refValue@pre(r) = self.RefObject::refValue(r))

Model:Constraint.name: ContentNamesMustNotCollide
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Namespace inv: self.contents.forAll(e1, e2 | e1.name = e2.name implies r1 = r2)

Model:Constraint.name: SupertypeMustNotBeSelf
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context GeneralizableElement inv: self.allSupertypes() -> forAll(s | s <> self)

Model:Constraint.name: SupertypeKindMustBeSame
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context GeneralizableElement inv: self.supertypes -> forAll(s | s.oclType() = self.oclType())

Model:Constraint.Model.ModelElement.name: ContentsMustNotCollideWithSupertypes
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context GeneralizableElement inv: let superContents = self.allSupertypes() -> collect(s | s.contents) in self.contents -> forAll(m1 | superContents -> forAll(m2 | m1.name = m2.name implies m1 = m2))

Model:Constraint.name: DiamondRuleMustBeObeyed
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context GeneralizableElement inv: let superNamespaces = self.supertypes -> collect(s | s.extendedNamespace) in superNamespaces -> asSet -> isUnique(s | s.name)

Model:Constraint.name: NoSupertypesAllowedForRoot
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context GeneralizableElement inv: self.isRoot implies self.supertypes -> isEmpty

Model:Constraint.name: SupertypesMustBeVisible
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context GeneralizableElement inv: self.supertypes -> forAll(s | self.isVisible(s))

Model:Constraint.name: NoSubtypesAllowedForLeaf
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context GeneralizableElement inv: self.supertypes -> forAll(s | not s.isLeaf)

Model:Constraint.name: AssociationsCannotBeTypes
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context TypedElement inv: not self.type.oclIsKindOf(Association)

Model:Constraint.name: TypeMustBeVisible
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context TypedElement inv: self.isVisible(self.type)

Model:Constraint.name: ClassContainmentRules
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Class inv: Set{Class, DataType, Attribute, Reference, Operation, Exception, Constant, Constraint, Tag} -> includesAll(self.contentTypes())

Model:Constraint.Model.ModelElement.name: AbstractClassesCannotBeSingleton
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Class inv: self.isAbstract implies not self.isSingleton

Model:Constraint.Model.ModelElement.name: LowerCannotBeNegativeOrUnbounded
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context MultiplicityType inv: self.lower >= 0 and self.lower <> Unbounded

Model:Constraint.name: LowerCannotExceedUpper
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context MultiplicityType inv: self.lower <= self.upper or self.upper = Unbounded

Model:Constraint.name: UpperMustBePositive
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context MultiplicityType inv: self.upper >= 1 or self.upper = Unbounded

Model:Constraint.name: MustBeUnorderedNonunique
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context MultiplicityType inv: self.upper = 1 implies (not self.isOrdered and not self.isUnique)

Model:Constraint.name: DataTypeContainmentRules
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context DataType inv: if self.oclIsOfType(StructureType) then Set{TypeAlias, Constraint, Tag, StructureField} -> includesAll(self.contentTypes()) else Set{TypeAlias, Constraint, Tag} -> includesAll(self.contentTypes())

Model:Constraint.name: DataTypesHaveNoSupertypes
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context DataType inv: self.supertypes -> isEmpty

Model:Constraint.name: DataTypesCannotBeAbstract
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context DataType inv: not self.isAbstract

Model:Constraint.name: MustHaveFields
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context StructureType inv: self.contents -> exists(c | c.oclIsOfType(StructureField))

Model:Constraint.name: StructureFieldContainmentRules
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context StructureField inv: Set{Constraint, Tag}) -> includesAll(self.contentTypes)

Model:Constraint.Model.ModelElement.name: ReferenceMultiplicityMustMatchEnd
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Reference inv: self.multiplicity = self.referencedEnd.multiplicity

Model:Constraint.name: ReferenceMustBeInstanceScoped
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Reference inv: self.scope = #instance_level

Model:Constraint.Model.ModelElement.name: ChangeableReferenceMustHaveChangeableEnd
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Reference inv: self.isChangeable = self.referencedEnd.isChangeable

Model:Constraint.name: ReferenceTypeMustMatchEndType
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Reference inv: self.type = self.referencedEnd.type

Model:Constraint.name: ReferencedEndMustBeNavigable
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Reference inv: self.referencedEnd.isNavigable

Model:Constraint.name: ContainerMustMatchExposedType
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Reference inv: self.container.allSupertypes() -> including(self) -> includes(self.referencedEnd.otherEnd.type)

Model:Constraint.name: ReferencedEndMustBeVisible
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Reference inv: self.isVisible(self.referencedEnd)

Model:Constraint.name: OperationContainmentRules
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Operation inv: Set{Parameter, Constraint, Tag} -> includesAll(self.contentTypes())

Model:Constraint.name: OperationsHaveAtMostOneReturn
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Operation inv: self.contents -> select(c | c.oclIsTypeOf(Parameter)) -> select(p : Parameter | p.direction = #return_dir) -> size < 2

Model:Constraint.Model.ModelElement.name: OperationExceptionsMustBeVisible
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Operation inv: self.exceptions -> forAll(e | self.isVisible(e))

Model:Constraint.name: ExceptionContainmentRules
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Exception inv: Set{Parameter, Tag}) -> includesAll(self.contentTypes())

Model:Constraint.Model.ModelElement.name: ExceptionsHaveOnlyOutParameters
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Exception inv: self.contents -> select(c | c.oclIsTypeOf(Parameter)) -> forAll(p : Parameter | p.direction = #out_dir)

Model:Constraint.name: AssociationContainmentRules
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Association inv: Set{AssociationEnd, Constraint, Tag} -> includesAll(self.contentTypes())

Model:Constraint.name: AssociationsHaveNoSupertypes
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Association inv: self.supertypes -> isEmpty

Model:Constraint.name: AssociationMustBeRootAndLeaf
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Association inv: self.isRoot and self.isLeaf

Model:Constraint.name: AssociationsCannotBeAbstract
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Association inv: not self.isAbstract

Model:Constraint.name: AssociationsMustBePublic
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Association inv: self.visibility = #public_vis

Model:Constraint.name: AssociationsMustBeBinary
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Association inv: self.contents -> select(c | c.oclIsTypeOf(AssociationEnd)) -> size = 2

Model:Constraint.name: EndTypeMustBeClass
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context AssociationEnd inv: self.type.oclIsTypeOf(Class)

Model:Constraint.name: EndsMustBeUnique
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context AssociationEnd inv: (self.multiplicity.upper > 1 or self.multiplicity.upper = UNBOUNDED) implies self.multiplicity.isUnique

Model:Constraint.name: CannotHaveTwoOrderedEnds
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context AssociationEnd inv: self.multiplicity.isOrdered implies not self.otherEnd.multiplicity.isOrdered

Model:Constraint.name: CannotHaveTwoAggregateEnds
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context AssociationEnd inv: self.aggregation <> #none implies self.otherEnd = #none

Model:Constraint.name: PackageContainmentRules
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Package inv: Set{Package, Class, DataType, Association, Exception, Constant, Constraint, Import, Tag}) -> includesAll(self.contentTypes)

Model:Constraint.name: PackagesCannotBeAbstract
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Package inv: not self.isAbstract

Model:Constraint.name: ImportedNamespaceMustBeVisible
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Import inv: self.container.isVisible(self.importedNamespace)

Model:Constraint.Model.ModelElement.name: CanOnlyImportPackagesAndClasses
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Import inv: self.imported.oclIsTypeOf(Class) or self.imported.oclIsTypeOf(Package)

Model:Constraint.name: CannotImportSelf
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Import inv: self.container <> self.imported

Model:Constraint.name: CannotImportNestedComponents
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Import inv: not self.container.allContents() -> includes(self.imported)

Model:Constraint.name: NestedPackagesCannotImport
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Import inv: self.container -> notEmpty implies self.container -> asSequence -> first -> container -> isEmpty

Model:Constraint.name: CannotConstrainThisElement
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Constraint inv: self.constrainedElements -> forAll(c | not Set{Constraint, Tag, Imports, Constant} -> includes(c.oclType())

Model:Constraint.name: ConstraintsLimitedToContainer
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Constraint inv: self.constrainedElements -> forAll(c | self.container.extendedNamespace() -> includes(c))

Model:Constraint.name: ConstantsValueMustMatchType
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Constant inv: ...

Model:Constraint.name: ConstantsTypeMustBePrimitive
Model:Constraint.Model.Constraint.expression: context Constant inv: self.type.oclIsOfType(PrimitiveType)
